==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Correctness
<hw>Cor*rect"ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The state or quality of being
correct; <as>as, the <ex>correctness</ex> of opinions or of manners;
<ex>correctness</ex> of taste; <ex>correctness</ex> in writing or
speaking; the <ex>correctness</ex> of a text or copy</as>.</def></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Accuracy; exactness; precision;
propriety.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Corrector</ent>⟦br⟧
